  MT=151 RESOLVED AND UNRESOLVED RESONANCE PARAMETERS             4735 1451
  RESOLVED RESONANCE REGION (MLBW FORMULA) : BELOW 0.125 KEV      4735 1451
    MOST PARAMETERS WERE BASED ON THE EXPERIMENTS BY ANUFRIEV ET  4735 1451
    AL./2/  AVERAGE RADIATION WIDTH OF 148 MEV/2/ WAS ADOPTED.    4735 1451
    TOTAL SPIN J WAS TENTATIVELY ESTIMATED WITH A RANDOM NUMBER   4735 1451
    METHOD.  NEUTRON ORBITAL ANGULAR MOMENTUM L WAS ESTIMATED WITH4735 1451
    A METHOD OF BOLLINGER AND THOMAS /3/.  A NEGATIVE RESONANCE AT4735 1451
    -2 EV WAS ADDED SO AS TO REPRODUCE THE THERMAL CAPTURE CROSS  4735 1451
    SECTIONS GIVEN BY MUGHABGHAB ET AL./4/                        4735 1451
                                                                  4735 1451
  UNRESOLVED RESONANCE REGION : 0.125 KEV - 100 KEV               4735 1451
    THE NEUTRON STRENGTH FUNCTIONS, S0, S1 AND S2 WERE CALCULATED 4735 1451
    WITH OPTICAL MODEL CODE CASTHY/5/.  THE OBSERVED LEVEL SPACING4735 1451
    WAS DETERMINED TO REPRODUCE THE CAPTURE CROSS SECTION         4735 1451
    CALCULATED WITH CASTHY.  THE EFFECTIVE SCATTERING RADIUS WAS  4735 1451
    OBTAINED FROM FITTING TO THE CALCULATED TOTAL CROSS SECTION AT4735 1451
    100 KEV.  THE RADIATION WIDTH GG WAS BASED ON THE SYSTEMATICS 4735 1451
    OF MEASURED VALUES FOR NEIGHBORING NUCLIDES.                  4735 1451
                                                                  4735 1451
  TYPICAL VALUES OF THE PARAMETERS AT 70 KEV:                     4735 1451
